 kept in a cool, dry place away from children. Make sure to follow any local guidelines for CPR and resuscitation techniques, as training is required to use such equipment effectively.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-4d00" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dxcExB gjNMyZ pf-286_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-kqGpvY OSjcf"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-285_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:8px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-284_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-brPMkR cnEYUf pf-221_ pf-heading-1-h3">How to use a CPR face shield</h3><p class="sc-iMWBWc laPXAE pf-223_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The face shield shown in the image is a resuscitation face shield used during mouth-to-mouth resuscitation to provide personal protection against cross-contamination. Here’s a step-by-step guide on how to use it based on the instructions from the packaging:</p><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-294_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:8px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-291_"><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-EROOM foKNLL pf-301_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-296_ pf-text-1"><strong>Open the shield</strong> - Ensure you have clean hands before handling the shield. Remove it from its packaging carefully.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-298_ pf-text-1"><strong>Place the shield</strong> - Place the clear polythene shield over the patient’s face. The round filter paper should be positioned directly over the patient’s mouth.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-300_ pf-text-1"><strong>Position and hold</strong> - Hold the shield as illustrated on the packaging, ensuring a secure placement with the filter pad over the mouth to allow airflow.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-303_ pf-text-1"><strong>Perform resuscitation</strong> - Begin mouth-to-mouth resuscitation by blowing through the filter while ensuring the shield stays in place.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-305_ pf-text-1"><strong>Single-use only</strong> - Once used, the face shield should be discarded appropriately.</li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-lnPyOc gUmbDa pf-293_"><img title="Life-Saving Techniques: A Guide to Using a CPR Face Shield Correctly - ComplyPlus™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" alt="Life-Saving Techniques A Guide to Using a CPR Face Shield Correctly - ComplyPlus™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:4a312d80-6154-4781-871e-bcec90b34fa2" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Life-Saving_Techniques_A_Guide_to_Using_a_CPR_Face_Shield_Correctly_-_ComplyPlus_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_9c8e88e2-7d75-417f-a57c-f8f54eb1f1f4.png?v=1728986748" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Life-Saving_Techniques_A_Guide_to_Using_a_CPR_Face_Shield_Correctly_-_ComplyPlus_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_9c8e88e2-7d75-417f-a57c-f8f54eb1f1f4.png?v=1728986748&width=550 550w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Life-Saving_Techniques_A_Guide_to_Using_a_CPR_Face_Shield_Correctly_-_ComplyPlus_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_9c8e88e2-7d75-417f-a57c-f8f54eb1f1f4.png?v=1728986748&width=768 768w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Life-Saving_Techniques_A_Guide_to_Using_a_CPR_Face_Shield_Correctly_-_ComplyPlus_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_9c8e88e2-7d75-417f-a57c-f8f54eb1f1f4.png?v=1728